title: Jinjia Li’s Resume
text: Full time student of the Brigham Young University - Idaho.

title: Jinjia Li’s Resume
text:
Education
Brigham Young University - Idaho, Rexburg, ID Expected 2024

Bachelor of Science in Business Finance
Minor: Business Analytics & Financial Planning

Coursework:
Intermediate Statistics, Advanced Financial Management, Financial Planning, Advanced Financial Modeling
Grant & Honor:

Secured a $13,414 grant from Brigham Young University-Idaho, distributed over two and a half years.
Led a team to third place in a school-wide competition by identifying and resolving a student problem, showcasing strong project management and problem-solving abilities.

title: Jinjia Li’s Resume
text:
Work History

Data Science Project Manager
Brigham Young University - Idaho, Rexburg, Idaho April 2024 - Present

Enhanced decision-making and operational efficiency by analyzing and visualizing data across over 18 school departments using Power BI, and creating customized templates for improved data accessibility.
Troubleshot and resolved Power BI issues daily, personalizing solutions to meet specific departmental requirements, thereby ensuring continuous operational effectiveness and user satisfaction.
Managed the overall team workload by assigning projects based on complexity and team members’ strengths, ensuring balanced distribution and optimal performance.



Finance Intern
The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints Meetinghouse Facilities Department, Salt Lake City Jan 2024 – Apr 2024

Managed a high volume of work orders, conducting thorough audits of an average of 200 orders each day to uphold financial integrity and regulatory compliance.
Collaborated closely with team members, vendors, and category managers, employing effective communication strategies to resolve inquiries and issues effectively within accounts payable and work order processing workflows.



Spreadsheet Analysis Teacher Assistant
Brigham Young University - Idaho, Rexburg, Idaho Jul 2023 – Dec 2023

Graded over 1,000 individually customized excel projects which included Pivot Tables, VLOOKUP, VBA code, SUMIFS, advanced graphs, IF statements, and 50 + more functions and formulas.
Implemented a reliable grading system that not only consistently met deadlines but also offered students accurate insights, thereby contributing to a conducive atmosphere for continuous improvement.

title: Jinjia Li’s Resume
text:
Service Experience

Student Mentor
Heber J. Grand, Rexburg, Idaho Aug 2022 – Dec 2022

Provided one-on-one support to two freshmen student help students adapting to college life and ensuring a smooth transition.
Delivered tailored guidance and resources, ensuring mentees accomplished grades of 70% or higher.
Engaged in weekly meetings and exchanges with fellow mentors, contributing to personal development and mentorship responsibilities.



Full-time Representative
The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints, London, England Jul 2019 – Aug 2021

Led 5-7 tours per day, offering informative experiences to individuals, youth groups, and families visiting the Visitors Center.
Hosted multiple events with audiences exceeding 100 attendees, ensuring memorable and engaging interactions.
Controlled and responded to an average of 30 daily online inquiries, addressing concerns through phone calls and chat support.
Collaborated with 8 international representatives, contributing to various work assignments and promoting a global perspective.

title: Jinjia Li’s Resume
text:
Skills

Computer Skills: Power Bi, MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint, SQL, R, Python, DAX Language, Tableau.
Certifications: Data Science (2024), Business Fundamentals (2024), Marketing Principles Simternship (2023).
